reviewText: I wasn't familiar with Alan Jackson music until after I heard the song "Remember When" on tv in a commercial. The moment I heard this song I had to order it, just for that one song. After receiving it from Amazon in only three days I clicked on #18 and re-play. After listening to "Remember When" for well over an hour I listened to the other tracks, and to my surprise they were all great. "Remember When" will always be at the top of my chart in music, and I'm a 60's & 70's rock n roll guy! I then had to order from Amazon the DVD, and I must say, I quickly became an Alan Jackson fan. The entire Alan Jackson Greatest Hits Volume II DVD is fabulous.
summary: A song that will enter your soul, "Remember When."

reviewText: Don't get me wrong I like Alan Jackson. Along with George Strait they are the finest singers of country today holding true to the traditional country music style. So much of it today is rock and roll masquerading as country.In Alans Vol 2 disc 1 they give you 18 selections. All good. In Disc 2 you only get 6 selections. Come on now Alan has more than enough hits out that they could have put more than 6 on the disc. Actually they all could have gone on disc 1. A lot of albums have 24 selections on them and more.I like whats there but I get the feeling that greed has gotten to the producers of this album and I keep feeling I was ripped off.
Title: N/A
